      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the caramel",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the {{caster-sugar}} for the caramel in a small saucepan over medium heat without stirring until it turns a deep amber colour. Remove from the heat and carefully pour in the warmed {{double-cream}} for the caramel. It will spit. Stir until smooth. Add the {{unsalted-butter}} for the caramel and {{sea-salt-fine}} for the caramel and stir until combined. Pour into a bowl and leave to cool at room temperature until thick and spoonable, about 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the brownie batter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 170°C fan. Butter and line a 20 cm square cake tin. Melt the {{dark-chocolate}} and {{unsalted-butter}} for the brownies together in a small saucepan over very low heat, stirring until smooth. Cool for 5 minutes. Whisk in the {{caster-sugar}} and {{light-brown-sugar}} for the brownies. Whisk in the {{eggs}} one at a time, then the {{vanilla-extract}}. Fold in the sifted {{plain-flour}}, {{cocoa-powder}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}} for the brownies until just combined. Pour into the prepared tin.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Swirl and bake, 26 to 28 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spoon the cooled caramel over the brownie batter in large spoonfuls. Use a skewer or the tip of a knife to create the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "caramel swirl",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yug430000l4v4kw28rjfm"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": drag the skewer through the batter in S-shapes, pulling the caramel through without fully mixing it in. Bake for 26 to 28 minutes until the edges are set and the centre is still soft. Cool completely in the tin before cutting, at least 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
